gurmukhi: ik, jwhr jhUr hYN ]ik, hwjr hjUr hYN ]
transliteration: Ki Zaahar Zahoor Hain|| Ki Haazar Hazoor Hain||
translation: That Thou art visible illumination. That Thou art All-Prevading.

transliteration: Hamesul Salaam Hain|| Samastul Kalaam Hain||150||
translation: That Thou art reveiver of Eternal conpliments. That Thou art Venerated by all. 150

gurmukhi: ik, swihb idmwg hYN ]ik, husnl crwg hYN ]
transliteration: Ki Saahib Dimaag Hain|| Ki Housnal Charaag Hain||
translation: That Thou art Most Intelligent. That Thou art the Lamp of Beauty.

gurmukhi: ik, kwml krIm hYN ]ik, rwjk rhIm hYN ]151]
transliteration: Ki Kaamal Daroom Hain|| Ki Raazak Rahoom Hain||151||
translation: That Thou art completely Generous. That Thou art Sustainer and Merciful.151.

gurmukhi: ik, rojI idhMd hYN ]ik, rwjk rihMd hYN ]
transliteration: Ki Rozi Dihind Hain|| Ki Raazak Rahind Hain||
translation: That Thou art Giver of Sustenance. That Thou art ever the Sustainer.

gurmukhi: krImul, kmwl hYN ]ik, husnul jmwl hYN ]152]
transliteration: Daroomul Kamaal Hain|| Ki Housnal Jamaal Hain||152||
translation: That Thou art the perfection of Generosity. That Thou art Most Beautiful. 152.

transliteration: Ghanoomul Khiraaj Hain|| Gareebul Nivaaz Hain||
translation: That Thou art the Penaliser of enemies. That Thou art the Supporter of the poor.

transliteration: Darooful Shikann Hain|| Hiraasul Fikann Hain||153||
translation: That Thou art the Destroyer of enemies That Thou art the remover of Fear. 153.

transliteration: Kalankan Pranaas Hain|| Samastul Nivaas Hain||
translation: That Thou art the Destroyer of blemishes. That Thou art the dweller in all.

transliteration: Agadjul Gadoom Hain|| Rajaaik Rahoom Hain||154||
translation: That Thou art invincible by enemies. That Thou art the Sustainer and Gracious. 154.

gurmukhi: smsqul, jubw hYN ]ik, swihb ikrw hYN ]
translation: That Thou art the Master of all languages. That Thou art the Most Glorious.

gurmukhi: ik, nrkM pRxws hYN ]bihsqul invws hYN ]155]
transliteration: Ki Narakan Pranaas Bahistul Nivaas Hain||155||
translation: That Thou art the Destroyer of hell. That Thou art the dweller in heaven.155.

gurmukhi: ik, srbul gvMn hYN ]hmysul, rvMn hYN ]
transliteration: Ki Sarabul Gadann Hain|| Hamesul Ravann Hain||
translation: That Thou art the Goer to all. That Thou art ever Blissful.
